The script does the following:
1. Resets the password to an easy one (The password for root becomes password)
2. Enables the remote desktop from Windows
3. Installs Chromium, Chrome, Firefox , Flash-Plugin lxde, ubuntu-gnome-desktop, tightvncserver and xrdp 
4. When windows connect to Unix using mstsc, xrdp environment opens with a terminal along with chrome.

Google Chrome and all other browsers will open, if the --no-sandbox option is given along with the respective browser command. 
It is needed for the root user. E.g. google-chrome --no-sandbox. 
A Terminal is also shown along with chrome whenever mstsc runs.
